Topic: Traps 4.2.6 RapidSSL Issue
Body: Hello Community,Â i hope some of you could help me understand something.So when the Traps agent 4.2.6 with Catalina support released, we had quiet some issues with our Catalina Agents. They always threw me a SSL Error. Turns out, that for MacOS Catalina, Wildcard Certificats arent allowed. I then made the switch to standard RapidSSL-Certificates for both of our Servers, which worked good for some time. Our existing Catalina Agents didn't have any problems with the certificates. But now with newer Catalina installations (10.15.3) there seems to be the same issue again. It says "Server certificate for host RapidSSL TLS RSA CA G1 is not allowed". Does that mean that RapidSSL Certificates in general arent allowed and could i fix this issue by going for COMODO Certificates?Looking forward to your answers.Â Kind regards

Author: JokinLete
Topic: Traps VDI license validation failed
Body: Hi,Â We have detected that the agents are not registering in the ESM console. If we check the agent's console, it shows that it's connecting correctly to the Server, but in the console the agent does not appear.Â If we force the heartbeat, the agent changes the status to unlincesed, and it appears in the console like unlicensed too. There are more than 6000 licenses free so we do not understand why it changes to unlicensed status.Â If we force once more the heartbeat, the status changes to correct, and it appears correctly in the ESM console. But after 5 minutes it disappears again from the console.Â After reviewing the configuration, we have disabled the check of the ESM of automatic license revocation. After we have changed this configuration, the agents have started connecting correctly. Also we have checked that some agents that are connected to the ESM have the last heartbeat from last week, and they are still running. So we do not kn ow if there is a reporting issue too.Â After disabling the check of the license revocation, we have checked that some VDI pools are not connecting to the ESM. They are having the same issue with the automatic license revocation disabled.Â Why can be this happen?Â Regards.Â

Topic: Traps ESM - Failed Email Notifications using Gmail SMTP-Relay
Body: Hello,Â I am currently running the Traps ESM v4.1.2 console and core on a single Windows Server 2016 environment. I have been unable to get email notifications to send. When I send a test message within Settings > ESM > Email, I receive the error "Failed to send test message." My organization is using Google Apps / G-Suite, and I have ensured that our smtp-relay rule allows for all addresses to send through SMTP without requiring SMTP authentication or TLS encryption. Within the email settings on the ESM, I have provided a valid user account and password. I tried using smtp-relay.gmail.com and smtp.gmail.com on ports 25, 465, and 587.Â Palo Alto Support has asked that I provide logs from Google's servers, which is not possible. Google support has assured me that nothing on their end should block smtp relays with my rule enabled. I am able to see the smtp traffic leave my network when I attempt to test notifications on the ESM. I also have several other services running on my network that use SMTP relay through Gmail and have no problems.Â Â Â I would appriciate any advise on this issue. Thank you.

Author: RLI27
Topic: ESM email configuration/behaviour in V4.2.4 changed?
Body: Hi communityUnder Settings->ESM->email you can configure email settings for reporting logging events by mail. This was working fine all the time up to ESM V4.2.3. Now last week we upgraded to V4.2.4 (minor...) and do not receive emails anymore.Button "Send Test Message" always results in "Failed to send test message" above in red... So checking the logs we see a error we would expect while using "enable SSL":"ERROR w3wp 63 Cyvera.Server.Facades.Reporting.Reporters.MailReporter Communication SSL Policy Error: RemoteCertificateNameMismatch, RemoteCertificateChainErrorsÂ "- but "enable SSL" is not ticked in our configuration.We found out that no matter if we tick "enable SSL" or not we can see on the exchange mail receiver side that the ESM Server always sends a STARTTLS - so this looks like a bug.We tried toÂ workaround the problem with presenting on the exchange mail receiver a valid certificateÂ and yes we came one step further - but just one. No the ESM shows in the logs that sender username and password cannot be empty:WARN w3wp 43 Cyvera.Server.Facades.Reporting.Reporters.MailReporter General "Failed to decrypt password. Error: Value cannot be null.Parameter name: s "ERROR w3wp 43 Cyvera.Management.Web.Controllers.AdministrationController General "Failed to send test mail message System.ArgumentNullException: Value cannot be null.Parameter name: userNameWe have a blank user name and password in the ESM GUI, because our mail receiver does not support authentication. So we are stuckÂ again... and yes we had the same configuration in V4.2.3 worked like a charm...Â So we are not able to report logging events by mail in ESM V4.3.4. Anybody seeing the same?Â Why this behaviours all changed withoutÂ any notice?Â Any help much appreciatedÂ

Author: Meteo-Admin
Topic: Our experience with traps. Unfortunately very bad!!!
Body: We ordered Traps because we had a very good experience with the Palaoalto Firewall's and the features of Traps sound good. We installed the ESM server, uninstalled our previous soloution (Trend Micro Worry-Free Business Soloution) and rollout the Traps client. Everything worked well. But with the first update came the problems. The update sometimes not work, the Traps service were missing or not started. We must reinstall clients manually often with the removal tool. With each update always the same problems!Then we heard from the Traps management service. In the hope that the problems do not occur with the Traps management service we migrated our configuration. Everthing works well again. But with the first update the same trouble.We order Traps from our dealer. It's a business partner from Paloalto. And therefore we can't open a support case directly by Paloalto. Two weeks ago our dealer told us it's a bug and it would be solved with the agent version 5.0.4. But we have the same problems with 5.0.4. Our dealer has never been able to help us but always want money for his support.Has anyone had the same experiences?

Author: Sandeep_R
Topic: Traps agent 4.2.0  installation error
Body: Hello Dears,Â Â When I tried installing Traps agent 4.2.0 , it rolled back the installation after it failed to start cyvera service. Then I disabled driver signature enforcement in windows and tried installing it, I was able to install agent without any issues. But when I restarted the machine again, Driver signing enforcement turned on and the Traps Agent services failed to start.Â We have installed traps on 300+ endpoints and mostÂ  of them are Windows 10 Machines.Â Currently only this one machine is having this issue. Earlier, during the initial deployment, I had issues with installation on couple of machines, but they all got resolved when I installed them in diagnostic boot with driver signing off.Again, when I tried disabling driver signing using BCDedit command, ( bcdedit /setÂ nointegritychecksÂ on ) I got error that the SecureBoot is enabled and it should be disabled to change Driver signing settings. When I rebooted the PC with Secure Boot disabled from BIOS, Traps started function normally, even with driver signing enforcement Enabled.Â Â It would be great if anyone can help me understand why did I faced this issue?Â Â - Is it the known issue in 4.2.0 ?- Will the Secure boot in windows will be enabled or disabled by default in windows?Â - How can the secure boot orÂ driver signing enforcement affect the Traps agent installation?Â Â Regards,SandeepÂ Â
Tags: , agent, driver signing enforcement, endpoint, installation, secure boot, TMS, traps, traps_agent

Author: dmilrad
Topic: New Traps Management Service Updates for September and October
Body: Every month new featuresÂ are introduced intoÂ the Traps management service.Â  To help you stay up to date we will post these new features here.Â  For more information click the link below to go to Traps technical documentation.Â Â Â 1. Role-based Access Controls:Â The following predefined roles provide access to the Traps management service to users based on their role and responsibilities.Â 2. On-Screen â€œWhatâ€™s Newâ€ Notification:Â On-screen display appears when new features are available with links for more details.Traps Management New Release NotificationÂ 3. Administrative Action Tracking:Â Allows admins to monitor the status of agent actions (upgrades, scans, and other activity) across multiple endpoints.Example of TRAPS Administrative Action TrackingÂ Â 4. DLL Blacklist for Exploit Protection:Â A blacklist can now be created as part of an Exploit Security ProfileÂ to prevent DLLs from running when launched by protected processes.Â 5. Examination of Office Files on Network Drives:Â Allows Traps to scan Microsoft Office files for malicious macros when the file is run from a network drive.Examine Office Files from Network DrivesÂ 6.Â Enhanced Management for Resolved Events:Â Allows you to close out one or more events without deleting them from the Traps management service.Â Â 7.Â Bulk Security Event Status Management:Â Simplifies management of multiple security events in bulk. For example, following an investigation on multiple endpoints you can change the status in one action.Â For more details on the new features, please refer to the following resources:

Author: MikeBourda
Topic: Issues with Traps VDI Tool sending hashes to Wildfire
Body: Traps ESM & Agent Version: 4.1.4Background: So thanks to help of Glen in the LiveCommunity, we've gotten up and on our feet with regards to using the Traps VDI Tool to assess our systems before enterprise-wide deployment.Â  The idea, of course, is to minimize the likelihood that Traps knocks over a legit process when we deploy en masse by using the Traps VDI tool to assess all of the hashes on a system, then identify all potential false positives, and adjust our master policy on the ESM appropriately.Â Issue: After kicking off a VDI Assetment with "Wait for Wildfire", the tool works for a bit, assessing hashes and what not, but we've been "stuck" for hours (like 12+ hours) at the same point (530 unknown samples to be submitted to Wildfire).Â  This has been the case for the last couple of days.Â What we've done: We've restarted this process a couple of times and get the same results.Â  Also, we've started from scratch, grabbing a new set of PE hashes with sigcheck.Â  Same results.Â  Also for the record:Â Any ideas?

Author: MikeBourda
Topic: Traps - Notification / Learning Mode for Initial Deployment?
Body: Background: This is a new deployment scenario in a small/medium-sized enterprise, about 5K hosts and 3K users.Â  LOTS of different, old/new applications and OS's.Â  Config mgmt is non-existant - it's the wild west.Â  Oh, and we have a development group, so there's some custom apps out there as well as new renditions popping up every so often.Â I'm *very* new to Traps and have been tasked to "make it work".Â  So far, I've got my ESM server and console up and Traps agents deployed to about 25 endpoints for testing, running with out-of-the-box default policies.Â  Things are going swimmingly from what I see - essentially no false positives.Â  I'm inclined to push this thing out to the whole org immediately.Â Unfortunately, my boss is less confident and is nervous about ticking off the end users and having a riot on our hands.Â  He's concerned that Traps will have a ton of false positives as we deploy it out to the end users and has directed me to put all policies in "notification mode" only.Â  The plan is to deploy department by department (OU by OU), so the idea is to have one set of policies for enforcement, and a duplicate set of policies set to notify only.Â  As we deploy and "soak" an OU, it will be in notify only mode.Â  After a few weeks, we want to move it to enforcement.Â  Once all OUs are moved into enforcement, we will delete the notify only policies. Â While I see the logic in that cautious approach, I don't see an easy way to do it within ESM.Â  It seems like we would have to somehow duplicate the default policies and go through hundreds of these policies, line by line and change the activation.Â  I see days to weeks worth of work just setting that up.Â  There's got to be an easier way.Â  OR I need someone to tell me "There's not really any way to do that so change your strategy".Any help or advice?Â

!!!!!2413104011.bmp------Â Â Â Â Â Â  06.01.2018Â Â Â Â  12:58Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  50238 !!!!!2389705127.docx------Â Â Â Â Â Â  13.12.2017Â Â Â Â  12:26Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  150000 !!!!!1076796588.xlsx------Â Â Â Â Â Â  06.01.2018Â Â Â Â  12:14Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  200000 !!!!!2824405210.ppt------Â Â Â Â Â Â  25.12.2017Â Â Â Â  11:50Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  249998 !!!!!2083205403.pptx------Â Â Â Â Â Â  13.12.2017Â Â Â Â  12:07Â Â Â  Â Â Â Â Â 300000 !!!!!2294358113.avi------Â Â Â Â Â Â  13.12.2017Â Â Â Â  13:04Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  350000 !!!!!2523101513.pstÂ Â Â With the cmd and the command dir, I don't see the files. Python sees, like the Powershell process, also the files Â«Python command (print(os.listdir('C:\\Users\\xxx\\Desktop\\')))Â»Â So I made an exclusion for the powershell. exe process, in which I deactivated the AntiRansomware module. After that the files are no longer visible with the command Get-ChildItem!!! *, but the python. exe process still sees the files. Means that the files are not actually present. These are really files simulated by traps for all processes. After the first default rule, this rule applies to all processes. After that, however, there are some compatibility rules where PaloAlto excludes the anti-ransom virus protection for certain processes. PaloALto has even more possibilities than us via GUI, they also have exclusions about the directories to be monitored.Â Now we know which files are being monitored, but not which actions. I understood this with powersehll. exe and python and came to this result:The following actions are monitored by traps (shown an alert):Â However, Traps does not recognize when a process recreates a file with exactly the same file name as one of these simulated files. Powershell. exe which sees these simulated files says about it:Â  Â  New-Item c:\Users\xxx\Desktop\!!!!!2126159552.doc -ItemType fileÂ  Â  New-Item : Die Datei "C:\Users\xxx\Desktop\!!!!!2126159552.doc"Â already existsCmd. exe which does not see the files means:Â  Â  C:\Users\xxx\Desktop>echo some-textÂ  > !!!!!2126159552.docÂ  Â  Access deniedÂ Â Either way, no traps alert is generated. Also there is no alert if the filename is appended with another character instead of !!!!!!! 2523101513. pst,!!!!!! 2523101515139. pst. This means that it only monitors these simulated files. A new Ransomware that writes other file names, even if they start with five exclamation marks or ZZZZ, will not give an alert.Â Therefore, I interpret the default rule parameter Ransom. HoneypotNamePatterns=ZZZZZ;!!!!! So that this is the fixed part of the filename of these simulated files, the numbers i think are random.Â Â What possibilities do we have for exclusion?Â Unfortunately, via Gui we have no possibility to make other exclusions than to exclude a corresponding process. I hope, however, that in the future we will be able to include the directories to be monitored in/exists and the files and file patterns to be simulated.Â I hope this could help a little bit

Author: MyBudget
Topic: MSI Installer default TEMP path triggering TRAPS notifications
Body: Hello Folks,Â Long time lurker, first time poster.Â Thought I'd share something I've come across with our TRAPS 4.1 deployment and some pesky "Media Control" restriction notifications and a solution that may be helpful for others.Â We're running our TRAPS install pretty much as it comes out of the box, not wanting to put in too many overrides just yet while I come up to speed with the system.Â Some of our physical servers have USB drives attached to them, with the USB drives being used as backup destinations for data that we need quick access to.Â I've noticed that when our servers that have these drives auto-patch overnight that TRAPS flags "attempted execution of executable from restricted location" on files such as "I:\8bb0d569f43ccb2c60051475\Setup.exe".Â  Now the MSI installer uses temporary file storage on whichever attached disk has the largest amount of free space, which in the case of these servers the USB drives.Â  And I assume that TRAPS is classing this as removable storage or such and flagging the issue.Â Rather than code up a TRAPS exception for this, I've done some digging around on the interwebs and have come across an article that explains how to configure the Windows MSI installer to use a fixed drive for MSI temporary file storage:Â https://serverfault.com/questions/372789/keep-windows-installer-from-using-largest-drive-for-tempora...Â It's a registry change, so it can be delivered on a server by server basis or by group policy if required.Â It appears to have stopped the TRAPS notifications as the files are running from an authorised location (non-removable media) and we have our temp MSI files being written to a pre-determined drive, something the control-freak in me appreciates.

Author: KRO-NCRV
Topic: MacOS - ROP Mitigation Firefox plugin-container
Body: Hi,Â I reported the following problem in a case:Â When an Â user visits Hotmail or Gmail with Firefox, user gets ROP mittigation notification. This does not happen with Safari or Chrome.Mac with 10.10.5We use ESM 4..0.0.24417 with content update 15-1078Â ROP chain utilization attempt detectedÂ And support came back with this answer:Â ItÂ  has been confirmed to be a FP, here is how you can stop getting this event again.Create the following policy:- go to Policies -> Exploit -> Protection Modules, click Add- select ROP Mitigation , then enter ninja mode - click on Components button and set C0 to OFF- under Process tab, add plugin-container.exe to the selected processes list.- name the policy under Name tab and click Apply.Maybe this can be helpfulÂ for you too.Â Kind regards,Michael

Author: Willian
Topic: Multi-ESM Behavior or Load Balancer
Body: Â Multi-ESM behavior and the use of load balancer are mutually exclusive. If you choose to use a load balancer, be sure to set all ESM Servers to "Disabled" in ESM Console's Settings > ESM > Multi-ESM tab. This setting does not disable the ESM Servers as whole; ESM Servers set to "Disabled" on this screen continue to operate as normal except that they do not participate in the Multi-ESM algorithm.Â If you fail to set the ESM Servers to "Disabled" in a load-balancer configuration, the consequece will be that endpoints learn about the serves as part of their regular heartbeat cycle and then might (depending on network topology) try to connect directly to an ESM Server instead of through your load balancer.Â The Multi-ESM AlgorithmÂ On each heartbeat, each endpoint:Â Deployment without Load BalancerÂ Deployment with Load BalancerÂ Â WillianÂ Â Â Â
Tags: , endpoint, esm, Load Balancer, Multi-ESM, TMS, traps

Author: gafrol
Topic: WF Machine Learning
Body: I just had a sample which was uploaded from ESM to WF. The analysis of WF showed an overall verdict of Malware even though static and dynamic analysis both are showing a benign verdict. I opened a case with TAC to clarify how this can be.Â Obviously with the newly designed WF there is a new machine learning alogorithm verdict which is currently not displayed in the WF Report. This verdict was Malware and therefore the overall verdict was Malware as well.Â Just to let you guys know should you stumble across the same issue.Â CheersRoland
Tags: , endpoint, machine learning, malware, TMS, traps, wildfire
